{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_b2fc7257dc324b28a8dee1c2","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here are the results of all four git commands.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Recent 20 Commits\n\n```\nf3cd732 fix: flatten reporting key in by_form_type view for data shape compatibility\ndce4064 feat: add GCS-backed last-updated timestamps to admin pages\nbc59f4a feat: add auth and missing user-report routes for admin pages\ne66e446 feat: wire dynamic TTC list from GCS on admin pages\nae72955 fix: correct test fixture endpoint path for integrity load\nb348a23 feat: wire reporting routes to real GCS data\n595121e fix: correct evaluation matching processCurrent/processLifetime nesting and reporting status placement\n79e7d86 feat: port user summary aggregation with evaluation matching\n33d3ea7 feat: add user data routes for form-data, instances, and config\nc61ffcf feat: wire form data persistence to GCS in upload endpoint\na5a8606 feat: port TTCPortalUser class for GCS-backed user persistence\nf09046c feat: port admin config CRUD with GCS persistence\nb0c8413 feat: port bounded Levenshtein distance for evaluation matching\nf003658 feat: add auth middleware with admin permissions and cron bypass\na147465 feat: port reporting status state machine from Python\n25ceece feat: add login endpoint with dev and production modes\n71875d6 feat: add GCS read/write utility\ne4550d6 docs: clearer setup instructions with clone/fetch options\n40152a7 docs: improve test plan with clear intro and setup for Alexei\n423ff1c docs: add Playwright QA screenshots for all 20 pages\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Files Changed in `f3cd732` (flatten reporting key commit)\n\n**One file changed** with 173 insertions and 2 deletions:\n\n- `app/utils/reporting/user-summary.ts` -- 175 lines changed (+173/-2)\n\nThe commit message explains: The `by_form_type` output (used by summary page client JS) expected flat reporting fields (`reporting_status`, `evaluations_reporting_status`, etc.) at top level with evaluations as arrays of full form instances. The `invertToByFormType` function was doing a simple key-swap that preserved the nested `reporting` wrapper, causing shape mismatches with the client JS. The fix also skips the `reporting` key at formType level to prevent it from appearing as a spurious TTC instance.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Full Diff of `f3cd732`\n\nThe diff adds four new functions and modifies `invertToByFormType` in `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/reporting/user-summary.ts`:\n\n**Modified function `invertToByFormType`** (lines 665-695):\n- Added logic to skip `KEY` (the `'reporting'` string) at both the `formType` level and the `instance` level during iteration.\n- Changed the inner loop to call `flattenForByFormType()` instead of doing a direct assignment, passing the full `byUser` context along with `email`, `formType`, and `instance` keys.\n\n**New function `flattenForByFormType`** (~55 lines):\n- Handles `fiEmail` nesting unwrapping (single-key objects whose inner value has `data` or `reporting`).\n- Promotes fields from the nested `reporting` sub-key to the top level.\n- For `ttc_application` form type, converts `evaluations` references into resolved full evaluation instance arrays via `resolveEvaluationReferences`.\n- Builds `lifetime_evaluations` from the formType-level reporting data via `resolveLifetimeEvaluationReferences`.\n- Converts `Set` instances to arrays for `lifetime_reporting_matched_ttc_list`.\n- Skips lifetime-only fields (`evaluations_submitted_count`, `latest_evaluation_datetime_est`) from per-instance promotion.\n\n**New function `resolveEvaluationReferences`** (~15 lines):\n- Takes an evaluations reference map `{ evaluatorEmail: { ve: name } }` and looks up each referenced evaluation in the `byUser` data, returning an array of full evaluation form instances.\n\n**New function `resolveLifetimeEvaluationReferences`** (~20 lines):\n- Takes a lifetime reference map `{ fi: { evaluatorEmail: { ve: name } } }` and resolves each to a full evaluation instance via `lookupEvaluation`.\n\n**New function `lookupEvaluation`** (~30 lines):\n- Traverses `byUser[evaluatorEmail]['ttc_evaluation'][fi][veKey]` to find a specific evaluation instance.\n- Flattens the `reporting` key on the evaluation instance before returning (promoting reporting fields to top level, converting Sets to arrays).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Task 6 / Data Shape / Mock Related Commits\n\nThe grep across all branches found exactly **2 matching commits**:\n\n```\nf3cd732 fix: flatten reporting key in by_form_type view for data shape compatibility\n1f7433d feat: add mock data for admin pages, Docker setup, and test plan\n```\n\nSo the only commit specifically addressing the data shape fix is `f3cd732` itself. The other match (`1f7433d`) is a mock data / Docker setup commit that matched on the word \"mock\" in the grep pattern."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"42310003-5b42-4a27-b087-b2860cdc53e2","uuid":"3671b28e-9745-474c-901b-71be01346536","timestamp":"2026-04-06T14:43:31.611Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"In /Users/m/ttp-split-experiment, run these git commands and report the results:\n\n1. `git log --oneline -20` to see recent commits\n2. `git show --stat f3cd732` to see what files were changed in the \"flatten reporting key\" commit\n3. `git diff f3cd732~1..f3cd732` to see the actual changes in that commit (the Task 6 data shape fix)\n\nAlso check `git log --oneline --all | grep -i \"data.*shape\\|shape.*compat\\|task.*6\\|mock\"` to find any other Task 6 related commits.","agentId":"ad4fd30f996eae3b2","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here are the results of all four git commands.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Recent 20 Commits\n\n```\nf3cd732 fix: flatten reporting key in by_form_type view for data shape compatibility\ndce4064 feat: add GCS-backed last-updated timestamps to admin pages\nbc59f4a feat: add auth and missing user-report routes for admin pages\ne66e446