{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_ae37c216220a47a08cd82df9","type":"tool_result","content":"1\timport { readJson, writeJson, GCS_PATHS } from './gcs';\n2\t\n3\texport async function getAdminConfig(): Promise<Record<string, unknown>> {\n4\t  try {\n5\t    const config = await readJson(GCS_PATHS.ADMIN_CONFIG) as Record<string, unknown>;\n6\t    return (config.raw_config as Record<string, unknown>) || {};\n7\t  } catch {\n8\t    // File not found — return empty config (matching legacy admin.py:78-80)\n9\t    return {};\n10\t  }\n11\t}\n12\t\n13\texport async function setAdminConfig(configParams: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> {\n14\t  // Read existing config\n15\t  let config: Record<string, unknown> = {};\n16\t  try {\n17\t    config = await readJson(GCS_PATHS.ADMIN_CONFIG) as Record<string, unknown>;\n18\t  } catch {\n19\t    // File not found — start fresh\n20\t  }\n21\t\n22\t  config.raw_config = configParams;\n23\t\n24\t  // Extract whitelisted user emails (matching legacy admin.py:47-53)\n25\t  const whitelistedEmails: string[] = [];\n26\t  const whitelistedUsers = configParams.i_whitelisted_user;\n27\t  if (Array.isArray(whitelistedUsers)) {\n28\t    for (const user of whitelistedUsers) {\n29\t      if (user && typeof user === 'object' && 'i_whitelisted_user_email' in user) {\n30\t        const email = (user as Record<string, unknown>).i_whitelisted_user_email;\n31\t        if (typeof email === 'string') {\n32\t          whitelistedEmails.push(email.trim().toLowerCase());\n33\t        }\n34\t      }\n35\t    }\n36\t  }\n37\t  config.whitelisted_user_emails = whitelistedEmails;\n38\t\n39\t  await writeJson(GCS_PATHS.ADMIN_CONFIG, config);\n40\t}\n41\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"42310003-5b42-4a27-b087-b2860cdc53e2","uuid":"06ae5585-3968-4a0a-b881-7f8f6dd8087d","timestamp":"2026-04-06T14:47:53.504Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/admin-config.ts","content":"import { readJson, writeJson, GCS_PATHS } from './gcs';\n\nexport async function getAdminConfig(): Promise<Record<string, unknown>> {\n  try {\n    const config = await readJson(GCS_PATHS.ADMIN_CONFIG) as Record<string, unknown>;\n    return (config.raw_config as Record<string, unknown>) || {};\n  } catch {\n    // File not found — return empty config (matching legacy admin.py:78-80)\n    return {};\n  }\n}\n\nexport async function setAdminConfig(configParams: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> {\n  // Read existing config\n  let config: Record<string, unknown> = {};\n  try {\n    config = await readJson(GCS_PATHS.ADMIN_CONFIG) as Record<string, unknown>;\n  } catch {\n    // File not found — start fresh\n  }\n\n  config.raw_config = configParams;\n\n  // Extract whitelisted user emails (matching legacy admin.py:47-53)\n  const whitelistedEmails: string[] = [];\n  const whitelistedUsers = configParams.i_whitelisted_user;\n  if (Array.isArray(whitelistedUsers)) {\n    for (const user of whitelistedUsers) {\n      if (user && typeof user === 'object' && 'i_whitelisted_user_email' in user) {\n        const email = (user as Record<string, unknown>).i_whitelisted_user_email;\n        if (typeof email === 'string') {\n          whitelistedEmails.push(email.trim().toLowerCase());\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  config.whitelisted_user_emails = whitelistedEmails;\n\n  await writeJson(GCS_PATHS.ADMIN_CONFIG, config);\n}\n","numLines":41,"startLine":1,"totalLines":41}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_20260406224754ce0661acb67b4874","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"glm-5.1","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me analyze each comparison:\n\n### 1. MOCK_SUMMARY_DATA vs by_form_type (get-by-form-type endpoint)\n\nThe by_form_type data is generated by `invertToByFormType` → `flattenForByFormType` and served directly from GCS.\n\n**Mock shape (per email in ttc_application.default):**\n```\n{\n  data: { i_fname, i_lname, i_cellphone, i_homephone, i_address_city, i_address_state },\n  reporting_status: \"complete\",\n  evaluations_reporting_status: \"complete\",\n  evaluations: [{ data, reporting_status, email, form_instance }],\n  lifetime_evaluations: [{ data, reporting_status, email, form_instance, ttc_metadata }],\n  form_instance: \"app-001\",\n  last_update_datetime_est: \"03/28/2026 14:30\",\n}\n```\n\n**Real code output (from flattenForByFormType):**\n- Copies top-level fields from unwrapped form instance: `data`, `form_instance`, `last_update_datetime_est`, `form_instance_page_data`, `is_form_submitted`, `is_form_complete`, `ttc_metadata`, `last_update_datetime`\n- Promotes from reporting sub-key: `reporting_status`, `evaluations_reporting_status`, `eval_teaching_readiness`, `eval_teaching_readiness_not_ready_now_count`, `evaluator_ratings_below_3`, `prereq_no_count`, and any `*_count` from array counting\n- Does NOT promote: `evaluations_submitted_count`, `latest_evaluation_datetime_est` (skipped in line 745-746)\n- Resolves `evaluations` → array of full evaluation instances\n- Resolves `lifetime_evaluations` from formType-level reporting\n\nThe real code would produce MORE fields than the mock, but includes all the mock fields. ✓\n\nWait, but does the real code skip `evaluations_submitted_count` and `latest_evaluation_datetime_est`? Looking at lines 745-746:\n```javascript\n} else if (k === 'evaluations_submitted_count' || k === 'latest_evaluation_datetime_est') {\n  //