e-level KEY\n        reporting_status: \"...\",\n        evaluations_reporting_status: \"...\",\n        prereq_no_count: 0,\n        enrolled_people_count: 45,   // only if i_enrolled_people is an array\n        org_courses_count: 8,         // only if i_org_courses is an array\n        evaluations: {},\n        eval_teaching_readiness: {},\n        eval_teaching_readiness_not_ready_now_count: 0,\n        evaluator_ratings_below_3: 0,\n        evaluations_submitted_count: 0,\n        latest_evaluation_datetime_est: '',\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\nHmm, the real code has extra fields in reporting that the mock doesn't: `evaluations_reporting_status`, `eval_teaching_readiness`, `evaluations_submitted_count`, `latest_evaluation_datetime_est`. But the mock has `prettc_date_to_deadline_days` that the real code doesn't produce.\n\nActually wait - I see `evaluations_reporting_status` in the KEYRESET section (line 229, it's set to empty but then later updated in the matching loop). And the mock has `evaluations_reporting_status` for MOCK_SUMMARY_DATA but NOT for MOCK_REPORTS_DATA. Hmm, let me re-check...\n\nLooking at MOCK_REPORTS_DATA's reporting:\n```\nreporting: {\n  reporting_status: \"complete\",\n  enrolled_people_count: 45,\n  prereq_no_count: 0,\n  eval_teaching_readiness_not_ready_now_count: 0,\n  evaluator_ratings_below_3: 0,\n  org_courses_count: 8,\n  prettc_date_to_deadline_days: 30,\n  evaluations: {},\n}\n```\n\nAnd the real code's per-instance reporting:\n```\nreporting: {\n  reporting_status: \"...\",\n  evaluations_reporting_status: \"...\",\n  evaluations: {},\n  eval_teaching_readiness: {},\n  eval_teaching_readiness_not_ready_now_count: 0,\n  evaluator_ratings_below_3: 0,\n  prereq_no_count: 0,\n  evaluations_submitted_count: 0,\n  latest_evaluation_datetime_est: '',\n}\n```\n\nDifferences:\n1. Mock has `enrolled_people_count` — real code would have it if `i_enrolled_people` is an array ✓\n2. Mock has `org_courses_count` — real code would have it