{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_d41afa825e354789b2412e53","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is the full report.\n\n---\n\n## 1. GCS_PATHS object (`/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/gcs.ts`)\n\n```ts\nexport const GCS_PATHS = {\n  USER_CONFIG_PREFIX: 'user_data/',\n  USER_SUMMARY_BY_USER: 'user_data/summary/user_summary_by_user.json',\n  USER_SUMMARY_BY_FORM_TYPE: 'user_data/summary/user_summary_by_form_type.json',\n  USER_INTEGRITY_BY_USER: 'user_data/integrity/user_integrity_by_user.json',\n  APPLICANT_ENROLLED_LIST: 'user_data/integrity/applicant_enrolled_list.csv',\n  ADMIN_CONFIG: 'config/admin_config.json',\n  FORM_CONFIG_PREFIX: 'config/forms/',\n  TTC_COUNTRY_AND_DATES: 'config/forms/ttc_country_and_dates.json',\n  TEMP_PREFIX: 'tmp/',\n} as const;\n```\n\nThe admin config GCS file lives at `config/admin_config.json`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `getAdminConfig` return behavior (`/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/admin-config.ts`)\n\n```ts\nexport async function getAdminConfig(): Promise<Record<string, unknown>> {\n  const config = await readJson(GCS_PATHS.ADMIN_CONFIG) as Record<string, unknown>;\n  return (config.raw_config as Record<string, unknown>) || {};\n}\n```\n\nIt reads the GCS file (which is a JSON object containing `raw_config` plus `whitelisted_user_emails`), unwraps `.raw_config`, and returns that inner object. On file-not-found, returns `{}`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. No test fixtures found\n\nNo files matched any of these patterns:\n- `test/**/admin_config*`\n- `test/**/config*`\n- `seed/**/admin*`\n- `seed/**/*config*`\n- `**/fixture*/**/*admin*`\n- `**/mock*/**/*admin*`\n\n---\n\n## 4. The settings data shape -- confirmed\n\nThe mock data at `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/api/admin/mock-data.ts` (lines 385-396) shows exactly what `getAdminConfig` returns:\n\n```ts\nexport const MOCK_SETTINGS_DATA = {\n  i_whitelisted_user: [\n    {\n      i_whitelisted_user_name: \"Admin User\",\n      i_whitelisted_user_email: \"admin@example.com\",\n    },\n    {\n      i_whitelisted_user_name: \"Test Coordinator\",\n      i_whitelisted_user_email: \"coordinator@example.com\",\n    },\n  ],\n};\n```\n\nThis is confirmed as the **return value of `getAdminConfig`** (i.e., the `raw_config` content). The shape is:\n\n```ts\n{\n  i_whitelisted_user: Array<{\n    i_whitelisted_user_name: string,\n    i_whitelisted_user_email: string\n  }>\n}\n```\n\nSo yes, `getAdminConfig` (the `get-config` endpoint's source data) returns exactly `{ i_whitelisted_user: [{ i_whitelisted_user_name, i_whitelisted_user_email }] }`.\n\nThe **full GCS file** stored at `config/admin_config.json` has a different outer shape -- it wraps the above inside `raw_config` and adds a denormalized `whitelisted_user_emails` flat array:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"raw_config\": {\n    \"i_whitelisted_user\": [\n      { \"i_whitelisted_user_name\": \"...\", \"i_whitelisted_user_email\": \"...\" }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"whitelisted_user_emails\": [\"admin@example.com\", \"coordinator@example.com\"]\n}\n```\n\nThis is consistent with the legacy Python code in `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/admin.py` (lines 41-53), which sets `_config['raw_config'] = config_params` and then extracts emails into `_config['whitelisted_user_emails']`."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"42310003-5b42-4a27-b087-b2860cdc53e2","uuid":"e5ff47b3-a3c5-4a67-bdda-40d51e840aa7","timestamp":"2026-04-06T14:52:16.587Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"In /Users/m/ttp-split-experiment, read these files and report their contents:\n\n1. `app/utils/gcs.ts` — show me the GCS_PATHS object (what paths are defined)\n2. `app/utils/admin-config.ts` — show me how getAdminConfig returns data (I already know it returns `config.raw_config`)\n3. The admin config GCS file structure — check if there's a seed/test fixture for admin_config that shows the expected shape\n\nAlso search for any test fixtures for admin config:\n- `test/**/admi