what `getAdminConfig` returns:\n\n```ts\nexport const MOCK_SETTINGS_DATA = {\n  i_whitelisted_user: [\n    {\n      i_whitelisted_user_name: \"Admin User\",\n      i_whitelisted_user_email: \"admin@example.com\",\n    },\n    {\n      i_whitelisted_user_name: \"Test Coordinator\",\n      i_whitelisted_user_email: \"coordinator@example.com\",\n    },\n  ],\n};\n```\n\nThis is confirmed as the **return value of `getAdminConfig`** (i.e., the `raw_config` content). The shape is:\n\n```ts\n{\n  i_whitelisted_user: Array<{\n    i_whitelisted_user_name: string,\n    i_whitelisted_user_email: string\n  }>\n}\n```\n\nSo yes, `getAdminConfig` (the `get-config` endpoint's source data) returns exactly `{ i_whitelisted_user: [{ i_whitelisted_user_name, i_whitelisted_user_email }] }`.\n\nThe **full GCS file** stored at `config/admin_config.json` has a different outer shape -- it wraps the above inside `raw_config` and adds a denormalized `whitelisted_user_emails` flat array:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"raw_config\": {\n    \"i_whitelisted_user\": [\n      { \"i_whitelisted_user_name\": \"...\", \"i_whitelisted_user_email\": \"...\" }\n    ]\n  },\n  \"whitelisted_user_emails\": [\"admin@example.com\", \"coordinator@example.com\"]\n}\n```\n\nThis is consistent with the legacy Python code in `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/admin.py` (lines 41-53), which sets `_config['raw_config'] = config_params` and then extracts emails into `_config['whitelisted_user_emails']`."}],"totalDurationMs":83952,"totalTokens":27330,"totalToolUseCount":13,"usage":{"input_tokens":1046,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":25472,"output_tokens":812,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
