{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_6f50ddaa1a5047ae89d90e70","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have all the information needed. Here is the complete report.\n\n---\n\n## Results\n\n### 1. `app/admin/ttc_applicants_summary/render.ts`\n\n**API response data read from `applicant_summary` object.** The JS fetches the summary data and iterates `applicant_summary['ttc_application'][selected_ttc]`.\n\n**Fields accessed from the API response:**\n\n| Field | Lines | How it is used |\n|---|---|---|\n| `reporting_status` | 98 | `_application['reporting_status']` -- read into `status` column data |\n| `evaluations_reporting_status` | 99 | `_application['evaluations_reporting_status']` -- read into `evals_status` column data |\n| `evaluations` | 89, 100, 103, 216-217 | `_application['evaluations']` -- defaulted to `[]` if missing, `.length` stored as `evals`, the full array stored for child row rendering |\n| `lifetime_evaluations` | 90, 101, 104, 241 | `_application['lifetime_evaluations']` -- same pattern, `.length` stored as `lifetime_evals`, full array stored |\n| `last_update_datetime_est` | 102 | `_application['last_update_datetime_est']` -- stored as `last_update_datetime` column data |\n| `is_reporting_matched` | 119 | `_evaluation['is_reporting_matched']` compared to `'N'` to find unmapped evaluations |\n| `lifetime_reporting_matched_ttc_list` | 120 | `_evaluation['lifetime_reporting_matched_ttc_list']` -- filtered against selected TTCs |\n| `reporting_status` (on evaluation child objects) | 225, 259 | `_e.reporting_status` / `_ev.reporting_status` -- rendered in child row detail |\n\n**Note:** `prettc_date_to_deadline_days`, `enrolled_people_count`, and `org_courses_count` are NOT accessed in this file. Those fields belong to the reports page only.\n\n**DataTable columns** (lines 162-167): `name`, `status`, `evals_status`, `evals`, `lifetime_evals`, `email`, `cellphone`, `homephone`, `city`, `state`, `last_update_datetime`.\n\n---\n\n### 2. `app/admin/ttc_applicants_integrity/render.ts`\n\n**API endpoint:** `$.get(\"integrity/user-integrity/get-by-user\")` (line 48). The parsed response is stored in `user_data`.\n\n**Fields accessed from the API response:**\n\n| Field | Lines | How it is used |\n|---|---|---|\n| `enrolled_matches` | 71-77, 96, 175-176 | `_applicant[key]['enrolled_matches']` -- iterated to count matches, full array stored for child row detail rendering |\n| `org_course_matches` | 80-85, 97, 193-194 | `_applicant[key]['org_course_matches']` -- same pattern |\n| `last_update_datetime_est` | 93 | `_application['last_update_datetime_est']` -- stored as `last_update_datetime` column data |\n| `i_enrolled_people` | 89 | `_application['data']['i_enrolled_people']` -- `Object.keys(...).length` used as denominator for enrolled matches display (`enrolled_matches_count + ' / ' + enrolled_people_count`) |\n| `i_org_courses` | 90 | `_application['data']['i_org_courses']` -- same pattern for org courses |\n\n**Important:** The actual fields `enrolled_people_count` and `org_courses_count` from your search list are NOT directly read from the API response in this file. Instead, the code computes counts from `i_enrolled_people` and `i_org_courses` objects at lines 89-90:\n```js\nvar enrolled_people_count = Object.keys(_application['data']['i_enrolled_people'] || {}).length;\nvar org_courses_count = Object.keys(_application['data']['i_org_courses'] || {}).length;\n```\n\nThe `integrity` field itself is not referenced by name in the JS template. The \"integrity\" concept is embodied by the `enrolled_matches` and `org_course_matches` arrays being non-empty (line 88: `if (enrolled_matches_count > 0 || org_course_matches_count > 0)`).\n\n**DataTable columns** (lines 124-126): `name`, `email`, `last_update_datetime`, `enrolled_matches_count`, `org_course_matches_count`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. `app/admin/ttc_applicants_reports/render.ts`\n\n**API response data read from `user_data`