N'` for unmapped evaluations |\n| `lifetime_reporting_matched_ttc_list` | 296 | `_eval['lifetime_reporting_matched_ttc_list']` -- filtered against selected TTCs |\n| `reporting_status` (on individual evaluations) | 466, 500 | `_e[rk].reporting_status` / `_ev[rk].reporting_status` -- rendered in child rows |\n\n**DataTable columns** (lines 352-366): `name`, `email`, `status`, `last_update_datetime`, `evals`, `lifetime_evals`, `evaluator_names`, `eval_teaching_readiness`, `evaluator_ratings_below_3`, `eval_volunteer_mental_fitness`, `age`, `gender`, `cellphone`, `homephone`, `city`, `state`, `org_courses_count`, `course_organized_count`, `course_assisted_count`, `intro_talk_count`, `enrollment_count`, `enrollment_list_count`, `prereq_no_count`, `prettc_teacher`, `prettc_date`, `prettc_date_to_deadline_days`, `prettc_location`, `youthteacher`, `course_wishlist`, `special_interest_groups`.\n\n---\n\n### 4. `app/admin/settings/render.ts`\n\n**API endpoints:**\n- **Load:** `$.get(\"admin/get-config\")` (line 160) -- returns JSON keyed by field IDs.\n- **Save:** `$.post(\"admin/set-config\", { config_params: JSON.stringify(_form_data) })` (line 145).\n\n**Fields accessed:**\n\n| Field | Lines | How it is used |\n|---|---|---|\n| `i_whitelisted_user` | 18, 249, 259, 262-263, 280 | Defined as a **repeater** field (line 18: `repeat_question_list` maps `\"i_whitelisted_user\"` to sub-fields `[\"i_whitelisted_user_name\", \"i_whitelisted_user_email\"]`). It is a `<select>` with `form-entry-type=\"repeater\"`. Options represent individual whitelisted user entries as JSON strings. |\n| `i_whitelisted_user_name` | 267-270 | Sub-field of the repeater; text `<input>` for the user's name |\n| `i_whitelisted_user_email` | 273-276 | Sub-field of the repeater; text `<input>` for the user's email |\n| `i_whitelisted_user_count` | 249 | Display-only `<span>` showing count of added users |\n\n**How the repeater works:**\n1. On **load** (line 158 `loadSettings()`): the response JSON has key