\\\\'' + encodeURIComponent(d.form_instance) + '\\\\');\">View Application (inline)</a>' +\n217\t    '</div>';\n218\t}\n219\t\n220\t$(document).ready(function() {\n221\t  $('#ttc_list').attr('multiple', 'multiple');\n222\t  $('#ttc_list').select2();\n223\t  get_user_data();\n224\t});\n225\t</script>`;\n226\t\n227\t  return `${pageStyles}\n228\t<div class=\"max-w-7xl mx-auto p-6 space-y-6\">\n229\t  <div class=\"text-2xl font-light text-gray-800\">\n230\t    ${escapeHtml(INTEGRITY_REPORT_TITLE)}\n231\t    <div class=\"text-sm text-gray-500 mt-1\">\n232\t      Please see below TTC applications for country\n233\t    </div>\n234\t  </div>\n235\t\n236\t  <div class=\"rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white shadow-sm p-6\">\n237\t    ${ttcListHtml}\n238\t  </div>\n239\t\n240\t  <div class=\"rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white shadow-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto\">\n241\t    <table id=\"${escapeHtmlAttr(INTEGRITY_TABLE_ID)}\" class=\"display nowrap cell-border w-full\">\n242\t      <thead class=\"font-light uppercase\">\n243\t        <tr>\n244\t          <th></th>\n245\t          <th>Name</th>\n246\t          <th>Email</th>\n247\t          <th>Last Updated<br><span class=\"text-sm text-gray-500\">(EST)</span></th>\n248\t          <th>Enrolled Matches</th>\n249\t          <th>Org Courses Matches</th>\n250\t        </tr>\n251\t      </thead>\n252\t      <tfoot>\n253\t        <tr>\n254\t          <th></th>\n255\t          <th colspan=\"5\" class=\"text-left\">Total Applications:</th>\n256\t        </tr>\n257\t      </tfoot>\n258\t    </table>\n259\t  </div>\n260\t\n261\t  <div class=\"text-sm italic text-gray-500\">\n262\t    Last updated ${escapeHtml(userIntegrityLastUpdatedDatetime)}\n263\t  </div>\n264\t\n265\t  <div id=\"step_post_submit_message\"></div>\n266\t</div>\n267\t${appScript}`;\n268\t}\n269\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"42310003-5b42-4a27-b087-b2860cdc53e2","uuid":"27e7f737-cf2b-4f20-a150-a18ed74102d6","timestamp":"2026-04-06T14:55:48.171Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/admin/ttc_applicants_integrity/render.ts","content":"import { escapeHtml, escapeHtmlAttr } from '../../utils/html';\nimport {\n  BUTTON_CSS,\n  DATATABLE_CSS,\n  DETAILS_CONTROL_CSS,\n  ERROR_MESSAGE_JS,\n  EXPORT_BUTTONS_JS,\n  FULLSCREEN_MESSAGE_JS,\n} from '../shared/datatables-helpers';\n\nexport const INTEGRITY_REPORT_TITLE = 'Admin: TTC Integrity Report';\nexport const INTEGRITY_TABLE_ID = 'ttc_applicants_summary';\n\nexport type IntegrityRenderOptions = {\n  integrityKey: string;\n  ttcListHtml: string;\n  userSummaryLastUpdatedDatetime: string;\n  userIntegrityLastUpdatedDatetime: string;\n};\n\nexport function renderIntegrityReport(options: IntegrityRenderOptions): string {\n  const { integrityKey, ttcListHtml, userSummaryLastUpdatedDatetime, userIntegrityLastUpdatedDatetime } = options;\n  const escapedKey = escapeHtml(integrityKey);\n\n  const pageStyles = `\n<style>\n  ${DETAILS_CONTROL_CSS}\n  ${DATATABLE_CSS}\n  ${BUTTON_CSS}\n  table.dataTable td, .dataTables_wrapper .dataTables_scroll div.dataTables_scrollBody>table>thead>tr>td,\n  .dataTables_wrapper .dataTables_scroll div.dataTables_scrollBody>table>tbody>tr>td {\n    vertical-align: top;\n  }\n</style>`;\n\n  const appScript = `\n<script type=\"text/javascript\">\nvar user_data = undefined;\nvar table = undefined;\nvar forms = {};\n\n${FULLSCREEN_MESSAGE_JS}\n\n${ERROR_MESSAGE_JS}\n\nfunction get_user_data() {\n  if (user_data) return;\n  $.get(\"integrity/user-integrity/get-by-user\", {})\n    .done(function(data) {\n      user_data = JSON.parse(data);\n      load_table_data();\n    })\n    .fail(function() {\n      postErrorMessage(\"There was an error retrieving the integrity data.\");\n    });\n}\n\nfunction get_table_data() {\n  var _selected_ttcs = $('#ttc_list').val() || [];\n  var applicant_data = [];\n\n  for (var _ae in user_data) {\n    if (user_data[_ae].hasOwnProperty('ttc_application')) {\n      var _applicant = user_data[_ae]['ttc_application'];\n      _selected_ttcs.forEach(function(_selected_ttc) {\n        if (_applicant.hasOwnProperty(_selected_ttc)) {\n          var _application = _applicant[_selected_ttc];\n          if ('data' in _application) {\n            var _name = _application['data']['i_fname'] + ' ' + _application['data']['i_lname'];\n            var enrolled_matches_count = 0;\n            if ('enrolled_matches' in _applicant['${escapedKey}']) {\n              for (var _me in _applicant['${escapedKey}']['enrolled_matches']) {\n                if (Object.hasOwnProperty.call(_applicant['${escapedKey}']['enrolled_matches'], _me)) {\n                  var _mee = _applicant['${escapedKey}']['enrolled_matches'][_me];\n                  if (Array.isArray(_mee)) enrolled_matches_count += _mee.length;\n                }\n              }\n            }\n            var org_course_matches_count = 0;\n            if ('org_course_matches' in _applicant['${escapedKey}']) {\n              for (var _me2 in _applicant['${escapedKey}']['org_course_matches']) {\n                if (Object.hasOwnProperty.call(_applicant['${escapedKey}']['org_course_matches'], _me2)) {\n                  var _mee2 = _applicant['${escapedKey}']['org_course_matches'][_me2];\n                  if (Array.isArray(_mee2)) org_course_matches_count += _mee2.length;\n                }\n              }\n            }\n            if (enrolled_matches_count > 0 || org_course_matches_count > 0) {\n              var enrolled_people_count = Object.keys(_application['data']['i_enrolled_people'] || {}).length;\n              var org_courses_count = Object.keys(_application['data']['i_org_courses'] || {}).length;\n              applicant_data.push({\n                name: _name, email: _ae,\n                last_update_datetime: _application['last_update_datetime_est'],\n                enrolled_matches_count: enrolled_matches_count + ' / ' + enrolled_people_count,\n                org_course_matches_count: org_course_matches_count + ' / ' + org_courses_count,\n                enrolled_matches: _applicant['${escapedKey}']['enrolled_matches'],\n                org_course_matches: _applicant['${escapedKey}']['org_course_matches'],\n                form_instance: _application['form_instance']\n              });\n            }\n          }\n        }\n      });\n    }\n  }\n  return applicant_data;\n}\n\nfunction load_table_data() {\n  var applicant_data = get_table_data();\n  if (table) {\n    table.clear();\n    table.rows.add(applicant_data);\n    table.draw();\n  } else {\n    table = $('#${INTEGRITY_TABLE_ID}').DataTable({\n      data: applicant_data,\n      orderCellsTop: true,\n      scrollX: true,\n      iDisplayLength: 50,\n      dom: 'Bfrtlip',\n      buttons: ${EXPORT_BUTTONS_JS},\n      columns: [\n        {className:'details-control', orderable:false, data:null, defaultContent:''},\n        {data:'name'}, {data:'email'}, {data:'last_update_datetime'},\n        {data:'enrolled_matches_count'}, {data:'org_course_matches_count'}\n      ],\n      order: [[1,'asc']]\n    });\n\n    $('#${INTEGRITY_TABLE_ID} tbody').on('click', 'td.details-control', function() {\n      var tr = $(this).closest('tr');\n      var row = table.row(tr);\n      if (row.child.isShown()) {\n        row.child.hide();\n        tr.removeClass('shown');\n      } else {\n        row.child(format(row.data())).show();\n        tr.addClass('shown');\n      }\n    });\n\n    // Search header\n    $('#${INTEGRITY_TABLE_ID} thead tr').clone(true).appendTo('#${INTEGRITY_TABLE_ID} thead');\n    $('#${INTEGRITY_TABLE_ID} thead tr:eq(1) th:not(:eq(0))').each(function(i) {\n      $(this).html('<input class=\"table_column_search_textbox\" type=\"textbox\" placeholder=\"Search\" />');\n      $('input', this).on('keyup change', function() {\n        if (table.column(i + 1).search() !== this.value) {\n          table.column(i + 1).search(this.value).draw();\n        }\n      });\n    });\n  }\n}\n\nfunction view_form(form_type, email, form_instance) {\n  $.get(\"reporting/user-report/get-user-application-html\",\n    {email:email, form_type:form_type, form_instance:form_instance})\n    .done(function(data) { postFullscreenMessage(data); })\n    .fail(function() { postErrorMessage(\"There was an error retrieving the application\"); });\n}\n\nfunction view_form_standalone(form_type, email, form_instance) {\n  window.open(\"reporting/user-report/get-user-application?email=\" +\n    encodeURIComponent(email) + \"&form_type=\" + encodeURIComponent(form_type) +\n    \"&form_instance=\" + encodeURIComponent(form_instance));\n}\n\nfunction format(d) {\n  var _tables = '';\n  var _forms = [{form_type:'ttc_application', email:d.email, form_instance:d.form_instance}];\n\n  if (d.email !== '') {\n    var _enrolled_match_rows = '';\n    for (var _mae in d.enrolled_matches) {\n      var _matches = d.enrolled_matches[_mae];\n      _enrolled_match_rows +=\n        '<tr><td class=\"bg-white\">Matched with Applicant:</td>' +\n        '<td class=\"bg-white border-r border-gray-200\">' + _mae + '</td></tr>';\n      for (var i = 0; i < _matches.length; i++) {\n        _enrolled_match_rows +=\n          '<tr><td class=\"bg-white\">' + (i+1) + '</td>' +\n          '<td class=\"bg-white border-r border-gray-200\">' + _matches[i] + '</td></tr>';\n      }\n    }\n    if (_enrolled_match_rows !== '') {\n      _tables += 'Enrolled Matches: <br>' +\n        '<table cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"0\" class=\"border border-gray-200 bg-white p-[13px]\">' +\n        _enrolled_match_rows + '</table><br>';\n    }\n\n    var _course_match_rows = '';\n    for (var _mae2 in d.org_course_matches) {\n      var _matches2 = d.org_course_matches[_mae2];\n      _course_match_rows +=\n        '<tr><td class=\"bg-white\">Matched with Applicant:</td>' +\n        '<td class=\"bg-white border-r border-gray-200\">' + _mae2 + '</td></tr>';\n      for (var j = 0; j < _matches2.length; j++) {\n        _course_match_rows +=\n          '<tr><td class=\"bg-white\">' + (j+1) + '</td>' +\n          '<td class=\"bg-white border-r border-gray-200\">' + _matches2[j] + '</td></tr>';\n      }\n    }\n    if (_course_match_rows !== '') {\n      _tables += 'Course matches: <br>' +\n        '<table cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"0\" class=\"border border-gray-200 bg-white p-[13px]\">' +\n        _course_match_rows + '</table><br>';\n    }\n  }\n\n  forms[d.email] = _forms;\n\n  return _tables +\n    '<div class=\"mt-[13px] mb-[7px]\">' +\n      '<a class=\"px-3 py-1.5 text-sm rounded-md border border-gray-300 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50\" onclick=\"view_form_standalone(\\\\'ttc_application\\\\',\\\\'' + encodeURIComponent(d.email) + '\\\\',\\\\'' + encodeURIComponent(d.form_instance) + '\\\\');\">View Application</a>&nbsp;' +\n      '<a class=\"px-3 py-1.5 text-sm rounded-md border border-gray-300 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50\" onclick=\"view_form(\\\\'ttc_application\\\\',\\\\'' + encodeURIComponent(d.email) + '\\\\',\\\\'' + encodeURIComponent(d.form_instance) + '\\\\');\">View Application (inline)</a>' +\n    '</div>';\n}\n\n$(document).ready(function() {\n  $('#ttc_list').attr('multiple', 'multiple');\n  $('#ttc_list').select2();\n  get_user_data();\n});\n</script>`;\n\n  return `${pageStyles}\n<div class=\"max-w-7xl mx-auto p-6 space-y-6\">\n  <div class=\"text-2xl font-light text-gray-800\">\n    ${escapeHtml(INTEGRITY_REPORT_TITLE)}\n    <div class=\"text-sm text-gray-500 mt-1\">\n      Please see below TTC applications for country\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white shadow-sm p-6\">\n    ${ttcListHtml}\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white shadow-sm p-4 overflow-x-auto\">\n    <table id=\"${escapeHtmlAttr(INTEGRITY_TABLE_ID)}\" class=\"display nowrap cell-border w-full\">\n      <thead class=\"font-light uppercase\">\n        <tr>\n          <th></th>\n          <th>Name</th>\n          <th>Email</th>\n          <th>Last Updated<br><span class=\"text-sm text-gray-500\">(EST)</span></th>\n          <th>Enrolled Matches</th>\n          <th>Org Courses Matches</th>\n        </tr>\n      </thead>\n      <tfoot>\n        <tr>\n          <th></th>\n          <th colspan=\"5\" class=\"text-left\">Total Applications:</th>\n        </tr>\n      </tfoot>\n    </table>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"text-sm italic text-gray-500\">\n    Last updated ${escapeHtml(userIntegrityLastUpdatedDatetime)}\n  </div>\n\n  <div id=\"step_post_submit_message\"></div>\n</div>\n${appScript}`;\n}\n","numLines":269,"startLine":1,"totalLines":269}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_202604062255495d9fffd3c30242a8","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"glm-5.1","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the integrity page JS access pattern. Let me trace through the code carefully:\n\n```javascript\nfor (var _ae in user_data) {\n  // _ae = email\n  if (user_data[_ae].hasOwnProperty('ttc_application')) {\n    var _applicant = user_data[_ae]['ttc_application'];\n    _selected_ttcs.forEach(function(_selected_ttc) {\n      // _selected_ttc = TTC instance key (e.g., 'default')\n      if (_applicant.hasOwnProperty(_selected_ttc)) {\n        var _application = _applicant[_selected_ttc];\n        // Check if 'data' exists at this level\n        if ('data' in _application) {\n          var _name = _application['data']['i_fname'] + ' ' + _application['data']['i_lname'];\n          // Look at _applicant['integrity'] for matches\n          if ('enrolled_matches' in _applicant['${escapedKey}']) { ... }\n          // _applicant['integrity']['enrolled_matches']\n        }\n      }\n    });\n  }\n}\n```\n\nSo the JS expects:\n- `user_data[email]['ttc_application'][selected_ttc]` to have a `data` field directly\n- `user_data[email]['ttc_application']['integrity']` to have `enrolled_matches` and `org_course_matches`\n\nNow, in the real integrity data from `loadUserIntegrity()`:\n\nThe structure produced is:\n```\nemail: {\n  ttc_application: {\n    integrity: {\n      enrolled_matches: {...},\n      org_course_matches: {},\n    },\n    fi: {  // form instance key (not 'default')\n      // If fiEmail:\n      fiEmail: { data: {...}, form_instance: \"...\" }\n      // If no fiEmail:\n      // data: {...}, form_instance: \"...\"\n    },\n  },\n}\n```\n\nWait, but the integrity code skips `default`:\n```javascript\nfor (const fiRaw of Object.keys(ud.form_data[ft])) {\n  if (fiRaw === 'default') continue;\n```\n\nSo the form instance key wouldn't be `default`. But the JS expects `selected_ttc` (which comes from the TTC list dropdown) as the key. If the user selects a TTC, the `selected_ttc` would be something like `europe-jan-2026` (from the TTC country and dates value). But in the form data, the instance key would be something different.\n\nActually, looking at how the TTC list works:\n- The TTC dropdown has options like `<option value=\"default\">Europe TTC (Jan 2026)</option>`\n- The value `default` maps to the TTC form instance key\n\nIn the user's form data, when they submit a TTC application, the form instance key would be `default-email@domain.com` (or similar). The fiEmail parsing would extract `fi = 'default'` and `fiEmail = 'email@domain.com'`. So the stored structure would be:\n```\nttc_application: {\n  default: {\n    \"email@domain.com\": { data: {...}, form_instance: \"default-email@domain.com\", ... }\n  },\n  integrity: { ... },\n}\n```\n\nBut the JS expects `_applicant['default']` to have `data` directly:\n```javascript\nif ('data' in _application) {\n```\n\nWith fiEmail nesting, `_applicant['default']` would be `{ \"email@domain.com\": { data: {...} } }`, and `'data' in _application` would be false because `data` is nested one level deeper under the email key.\n\nThis is a **SHAPE MISMATCH**! The integrity code creates fiEmail nesting, but the JS expects the data to be at the instance level directly.\n\nWait, but the same pattern exists in the Python code. How did the Python code handle this?\n\nActually, looking at the mock data again:\n```javascript\n\"maria.garcia@example.com\": {\n  ttc_application: {\n    default: {\n      data: {\n        i_fname: \"Maria\",\n        i_lname: \"Garcia\",\n        i_enrolled_people: { p1: \"John\", p2: \"Sarah\", p3: \"Mike\" },\n        i_org_courses: { c1: \"HP Barcelona\", c2: \"YES Paris\" },\n      },\n      last_update_datetime_est: \"03/28/2026 14:30\",\n      form_instance: \"app-001\",\n    },\n    integrity: {\n      enrolled_matches: {...},\n      org_course_matches: {},\n    },\n  },\n},\n```\n\nThe mock shows `default` containing `data`, `last_update_datetime_est`, `form_instance` directly — no fiEmail nesting. But the real code would create fiEmail nesting for form instances like `default-email@domain.com`.\n\nHowever, looking at the mock more carefully, `form_instance` is `\"app-001\"`, not `\"default-email@domain.com\"`. So the mock uses a different form instance key format.\n\nHmm, but in the integrity code, the form instance key is `fiRaw` (from the user's form_data). In the GCS-stored form data, the keys under `form_data.ttc_application` would be the form instance identifiers. These could be like `default-email@domain.com` or just `default` or a TTC-specific key.\n\nWait, looking at the integrity code again:\n```javascript\nfor (const fiRaw of Object.keys(ud.form_data[ft])) {\n  if (fiRaw === 'default') continue;\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nIt skips `default` form instances. So `fiRaw` would be something like `europe-jan-2026-email@domain.com` or similar.\n\nAfter fiEmail parsing:\n- fiRaw = `europe-jan-2026-email@domain.com`\n- fiArr = `['europe', 'jan', '2026', 'email@domain.com']`\n- fiArr.length >= 2 ✓\n- fiArr[1] = 'jan', doesn't include '@' ✓\n- fiEmail = fiArr[0] = 'europe'\n- fi = fiArr[1] = 'jan'\n\nWait, that's wrong! The split by `-` splits into ALL parts, but the code only takes `fiArr[0]` and `fiArr[1]`:\n```javascript\nconst fiArr = fiRaw.split('-');\nif (fiArr.length >= 2 && !fiArr[1].includes('@')) {\n  fiEmail = fiArr[0];\n  fi = fiArr[1];\n} else {\n  fi = fiArr[0];\n  fiEmail = fiArr[1] || null;\n}\n```\n\nFor `fiRaw = 'europe-jan-2026-email@domain.com'`:\n- fiArr = ['europe', 'jan', '2026', 'email@domain.com']\n- fiArr[1] = 'jan', doesn't include '@' ✓\n- fiEmail = 'europe'\n- fi = 'jan'\n\nThat seems wrong — 'europe' and 'jan' are fragments of the form instance key, not meaningful identifiers. But the Python code probably works the same way (since this is a port).\n\nActually, looking at the Python form instance key format in the mock: `form_instance: \"app-001\"`. This doesn't contain `-`, so `fi` would just be `\"app-001\"` and `fiEmail` would be null. Then `ftData['app-001'] = fd` directly — no email nesting.\n\nBut in the real user form data in GCS, the form instance keys are like the values from the TTC country and dates dropdown. For example, `default-email@domain.com` or `europe-jan-2026`.\n\nHmm, I think I'm overthinking this. The key point is that the mock data and the real data need to have the same shape. The mock shows no fiEmail nesting, and the JS code expects no fiEmail nesting. If the real data has fiEmail nesting, the JS won't work.\n\nBut this depends on what the actual form instance keys look like in the stored user data. If the keys don't contain `-`, there's no fiEmail extraction and no nesting. If they do contain `-`, there IS nesting.\n\nThis is actually an existing issue with the data pipeline, not specifically a Task 6 bug. The integrity code was ported from Python and should produce the same shape as the Python code.\n\nLet me focus on the specific bugs that Task 6 should have caught and fixed:\n\n1. **`last_update_datetime_est` in integrity**: The integrity load doesn't convert `last_update_datetime` to `last_update_datetime_est`. The integrity page JS reads `_application['last_update_datetime_est']` at line 93. If this field is missing, the table column shows `undefined`.\n\nThis IS a bug that should be fixed.\n\n2. **`prettc_date_to_deadline_days`**: Computed client-side. No issue.\n\n3. **`enrolled_people_count` in reports**: Computed from array fields in the summary load. Present in reporting sub-key. ✓\n\n4. **Settings shape**: Matches. ✓\n\nLet me also check if there are any issues with the by_form_type view (the main fix from f3cd732).\n\nActually, let me also check the reports page render.ts to understand the `_application[rk]` pattern better.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"42310003-5b42-4a27-b087-b2860cdc53e2","uuid":"6dceecbd-ceb1-433c-bdcc-e5b4f596d063"}
