{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_202604062300101fc701ac08a744f7","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"glm-5.1","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"TypeScript compilation passes. Now let me also verify the other data shapes are correct by checking the reports page's field naming.\n\nLooking at the reports page JS again:\n\nLine 147: `_application['${rk}']['eval_teaching_readiness_not_ready_now_count']`\nBut in user-summary.ts line 231: `fiReporting['eval_teaching_readiness_not_ready_now_count'] = 0;`\n\nWait, but line 147 in the reports render says: `eval_teaching_readiness_not_ready_now_count`\nAnd line 150 says: `lifetime_eval_teaching_readiness_not_ready_now_count`\n\nBut in user-summary.ts line 220-221:\n```\nttcAppReporting['lifetime_eval_teaching_readiness_not_ready_now_count'] = 0;\n```\n\nAnd line 231:\n```\nfiReporting['eval_teaching_readiness_not_ready_now_count'] = 0;\n```\n\nThese match. ✓\n\nLine 153: `_application['${rk}']['evaluator_ratings_below_3']`\nuser-summary.ts line 232: `fiReporting['evaluator_ratings_below_3'] = 0;`\n\nHmm wait, the reports page JS line 153 uses `evaluator_ratings_below_3`, but the reports page JS at line 240 uses `_application['${rk}']['evaluator_ratings_below_3']`. And user-summary.ts line 232 uses `evaluator_ratings_below_3`.\n\nBut in the KEYRESET (line 232): `fiReporting['evaluator_ratings_below_3'] = 0;`\nAnd later (line 463): `afiReporting['evaluator_ratings_below_3'] = ...`\n\nSo the name is `evaluator_ratings_below_3`. But the report_filter at line 153 reads `_application['${rk}']['evaluator_ratings_below_3']`.\n\nWait, line 153: `_application['${rk}']['evaluator_ratings_below_3']`. But line 240 reads the same: `_application['${rk}']['evaluator_ratings_below_3']`.\n\nOK these all match. ✓\n\nWhat about line 147: `eval_teaching_readiness_not_ready_now_count` vs what the code produces. The code at line 448: `afiReporting['eval_teaching_readiness_not_ready_now_count']`. ✓\n\nNow, the reports page at